Creating a Minecraft mod for both Java (Forge) and Bedrock is quite an undertaking, as each platform has its own set of APIs and conventions. Below is a simple example of how you might start implementing a basic "Terraburrow: Subterra" mod in Forge 1.21. This example will focus on setting up the main class and some basic mechanics for managing tunnels.

